Wires up the front gate keeper mobile app, which previously had a UI
shell but no functional backend (every call 404'd).

- gateStats() → GET /mobile/front-office/gate/stats — entries today,
  exits today, visitors in (still on campus), visitors today, open
  passes (Approved/Exited).
- verifyGatePass(token) → GET /mobile/front-office/gate-passes/verify/
  {token} — looks up the pass by QR token, returns holder + status +
  the next valid action (exit/entry) so the mobile UI doesn't have to
  encode the state machine.
- gatePassExit(id) / gatePassEntry(id) → POST endpoints that perform
  the Approved → Exited and Exited → Returned transitions and stamp
  exit_time / return_time. Invalid transitions return 422.
- visitorList() → GET /mobile/front-office/visitors — most-recent-first
  list (capped 100), supports ?today=1 filter.
- logVisitor() → POST /mobile/front-office/visitors — walk-in entry
  (validates name + purpose; in_time = now).
- visitorExit(id) → POST .../visitors/{id}/exit — sets out_time = now;
  rejects double-exit.

Pure controller + routes — no migration. School scope enforced via
school_id on every query.

Mobile half (QR scanner, log-visitor screen, refresh, notifications
tab) ships with the next Expo build.

